[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf?p=activemq.git;h=27238b2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf?p=activemq.git;h=27238b2&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-6535&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-6535&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fixing the auto+nio+ssl transport so that the protocol detection task&lt;br/&gt;
will properly terminate on timeout and not continue to run. Also&lt;br/&gt;
lowered the default detection timeout to 15 seconds instead of 30&lt;br/&gt;
seconds to match the InactivityMonitor default.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15742382" author="jira-bot" created="Mon, 12 Dec 2016 16:26:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit ae30662fbdc2bc263e7c7c2e3cda3f8bbb063907 in activemq&apos;s branch refs/heads/activemq-5.14.x from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=cshannon&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;cshannon&quot;&gt;cshannon&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf?p=activemq.git;h=ae30662&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf?p=activemq.git;h=ae30662&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-6535&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-6535&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fixing the auto+nio+ssl transport so that the protocol detection task&lt;br/&gt;
will properly terminate on timeout and not continue to run. Also&lt;br/&gt;
lowered the default detection timeout to 15 seconds instead of 30&lt;br/&gt;
seconds to match the InactivityMonitor default.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(cherry picked from commit 27238b2dd790cea38d95da46b23ed141f5847782)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15742384" author="christopher.l.shannon" created="Mon, 12 Dec 2016 16:27:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed by allowing the task to check if the thread was interrupted.  Also lowered the default timeout to 15 seconds.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
